{
  "texts": [
    "However, it is clear that these objects, when constructed using different such choices, are canonically related by similar constructions as above.",
    "The previous discussion shows that the map Φ is well-defined.",
    "That Φ is Hequivariant follows directly from (6), and from the fact that passing between minimal framings at a baspoint datum and at a direction is H-equivariant.",
    "That Φ is a bijection follows immediately from the fact that the Fourier transform is invertible.",
    "Finally, that Φ is algebraic follows from the fact that, following the algorithm in Theorem 5.3, the entries of the Stokes matrices of the Fourier transform, corresponding via the choice of minimal framing to the monodromies of the Stokes local system V along the paths shown in Figure 4 are -up to a sign -entries of products of the initial Stokes matrices and formal monodromy matrix, and in turn polynomial expressions in the entries of the initial Stokes data."
  ]
}